# cursor-usage-menubar

Lightweight macOS menu bar app (Python 3.9+, `rumps`, PyObjC `AppKit`) showing Cursor plan & usage from `https://cursor.com/api/usage-summary`.

## Key files

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `app.py` | Main app: icon (NSImage), fetch, menu, notifications |
| `login_window.py` | WKWebView sign-in on cursor.com/settings |
| `install.sh` / `uninstall.sh` | Install deps + optional LaunchAgent |
| `requirements.txt` | `rumps`, `pyobjc-framework-*`, `cryptography` |

## Rules

- **Network**: only `cursor.com` (usage API + login page + dashboard link). No telemetry.
- **Token**: `~/Library/Application Support/cursor-usage/config.json` — never commit; `.gitignore` covers it.
- **UI thread**: background fetch → `_pending` dict → `rumps.Timer` applies icon/menu on main thread.
- **Menu bar only**: `NSApplicationActivationPolicyAccessory` — no Dock icon.
- **Icon**: two stacked % + days/USD via `build_status_icon()`; show `<1%` when 0 < pct < 1.
- **Legacy**: `get_token.py`, `get_token_cdp.py` are deprecated (use `login_window.py`); listed in `.gitignore`.

## Run / test

```bash
cd "$(dirname "$0")/.." && python3 app.py
# or: bash start.sh
```

## LaunchAgent note

`install.sh` copies the app to `~/Library/Application Support/cursor-usage/menubar/` — launchd cannot read `~/Documents/` (TCC). Do not point the plist at the git clone under Documents.

